{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0161C72X1yRgKargqKiR1qsT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Root cause:** The `es-secure-settings` Secret (containing `s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key`) was already mounted at `/run/secrets/es-secure` on every pod, but the credentials had never been imported into the Elasticsearch keystore. Elasticsearch reads S3 credentials from its encrypted keystore, not from mounted files or env vars.\n\n**Steps taken:**\n\n1. **Populated the keystore on all 3 nodes** — Exec'd into `elasticsearch-0`, `es-data-new-0`, and `es-data-new-1` and ran `elasticsearch-keystore add -f` piping the values from the mounted secret files. This keeps credentials out of `elasticsearch.yml` and env vars as required.\n\n2. **Reloaded secure settings without restarting** — Called `POST /_nodes/reload_secure_settings`, which returned `successful: 3 / failed: 0` across all nodes. No pod restarts needed.\n\n3. **Registered the `minio-repo` snapshot repository** — PUT to `/_snapshot/minio-repo` with type `s3`, bucket `es-backups`, client `default`. The S3 endpoint (`minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local:9000`), protocol (`http`), and path-style access were already configured in `elasticsearch.yml`.\n\n4. **Verified with a successful snapshot** — `snapshot-2` completed in 1 second with `state: SUCCESS`, 2 shards, 0 failures."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":279,"cache_read_input_tokens":42332,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":279},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"762c68f5-1845-4b98-81fa-231425769761","uuid":"6037b54d-939f-4255-9a1c-a9d9b63e746a","request